title: Selected Topics in Biochemistry
description: Discussion of specialized topics related to the research interests of the members of the Centre. For example, recent offerings have included: Metalloproteins and Metalloenzymes; Heme Proteins; Chemistry of Enzymatic Reaction Mechanisms; Peptides - Synthesis, Structure and Function; Food Enzymology; Advanced Microbial Physicology; NMR in Biological Systems.

title: Enzymes
description: Discussion of the underlying factors contributing to enzyme, abzyme and ribozyme catalysis.

title: Selected Topics in Physical Chemistry
description: Discussion of specialized topics related to the research interests of members of the Centre. Special topics could include for example: principles of magnetic resonance in biological systems; collisions, spectroscopy and intermolecular forces, surface chemistry; catalysis; electrolyte theory; non-electrolyte solution theory; thermodynamics of biological systems; thermodynamics.

title: Master's Seminar
description: A public seminar and defence of a research proposal, to be given by all MSc students within two terms of entering this program.

title: General Chemistry 1
description: The stoichiometry of compounds and chemical reactions. Properties of gases. Periodicity and chemical bonding. Energy changes in chemical systems. Electronic structure of atoms and molecules; correlation with the chemical reactivity of common elements, inorganic and organic compounds.
requirementsDescription: Antireq: CHEM 121

title: General Chemistry Laboratory 1
description: Selected experiments based on introductory-level chemistry topics. This course is an introduction to the chemistry laboratory environment and focuses on the development of basic lab skills.
requirementsDescription: Coreq: CHEM 120. Antireq: CHEM 121L

title: General Chemistry 2
description: Properties of liquids and solutions. Introduction to chemical equilibria. Principles of acid-base equilibria, solubility and electrochemical processes. Chemical kinetics.
requirementsDescription: Prereq: CHEM 120 or CHE 102. Antireq: CHEM 125

title: General Chemistry Laboratory 2
description: Selected experiments based on introductory-level chemistry topics. This course is a continuation of CHEM120L, with increased emphasis on assessment of experimental design.
requirementsDescription: Prereq: CHEM 120L. Coreq: CHEM 123. Antireq: CHEM 125L

title: Structure and Bonding
description: An introduction to the principles of chemical structure and bonding, with emphasis on their application to inorganic systems. Topics include atoms, orbitals, and periodicity; localized bonding models; symmetry and group theory; and molecular orbital theory. The subjects treated in this course are foundational components for advanced studies in all areas of chemistry.
requirementsDescription: Prereq: CHEM 120, 123 or CHEM 121, 125; Honours students only

title: Multi-Component Analysis
description: Instrumental analytical chemistry, including traditional and more recent methods. Emphasis on planning and decision-making in the analytical process.
requirementsDescription: Prereq: CHEM 220, 220L.

title: Analytical Instrumentation Laboratory
description: Extensive lab experience for students who have taken CHEM220.
requirementsDescription: Prereq: CHEM 220 and CHEM 220L; Honours Biochemistry, Chemistry or Medicinal Chemistry students only.

title: Fundamentals of Biochemistry
description: Chemistry of amino acids, carbohydrates, lipids and nucleic acids, with special emphasis on representative proteins and enzymes, including hemoglobin, cytochrome c and chymotrypsin.
requirementsDescription: Prereq: CHEM 264 or 262; Honours Biochemistry, Biology, Chemistry, Environmental Science or Medicinal Chemistry. Antireq: CHEM 237, CHEM 239, NE 224

title: Introductory Biochemistry
description: An introduction to the chemistry of amino acids, carbohydrates, lipids, and nucleic acids. Structure and properties of proteins and enzymes.
requirementsDescription: Prereq: One of CHEM 262, 264, 266. Antireq: CHEM 233, CHEM 239, NE 224

title: Introductory Biochemistry Laboratory
description: Selected experiments for students taking CHEM237.
requirementsDescription: Coreq: CHEM 237

title: Introductory Chemical Thermodynamics
description: An introduction to the first, second, and third laws of thermodynamics and the application of these laws to ideal systems, mixtures, and chemical reactions. Thermodynamic principles are used to study changes in state, including phase changes, and to establish the link between the equilibrium constant and the properties of the substances involved in a chemical reaction.
requirementsDescription: Prereq: CHEM 123 or CHEM 125; One of MATH 128, 138, 148; Honours students only. Antireq: PHYS 358, ECE 403

title: Organic Chemistry 1
description: Structure and bonding in organic chemistry. Isomerism and stereoisomerism in organic compounds. Acidity of organic compounds and substituent effects on acidity. Reaction mechanisms and energetics. Chemistry of alkanes, haloalkanes, alcohols and ethers, alkenes and alkynes.
requirementsDescription: Prereq: CHEM 123 or CHEM 125; Honours students only. Antireq: CHEM 262, 266, NE 122/222

title: Organic Chemistry 2
description: Nucleophilic addition and substitution at CO carbon. Aromaticity and simple MO theory of conjugated systems. Electrophilic and nucleophilic aromatic substitution reactions. Applications of spectroscopic techniques in organic chemistry.
requirementsDescription: Prereq: CHEM 264; Honours students only. Antireq: CHEM 267

title: Organic Chemistry Laboratory 1
description: Selected experiments for students taking CHEM265.
requirementsDescription: Prereq: CHEM 123L or CHEM 125L; Honours Biochemistry, Chemistry, Medicinal Chemistry, or Science and Business (BIOCHEM) students only. Coreq: CHEM 265

title: Basic Organic Chemistry 1
description: Structure, nomenclature, and reactions of important classes of organic compounds. Stereochemistry and its role in reaction mechanisms.
requirementsDescription: Prereq: CHEM 123 or 125. Antireq: CHEM 262, 264, NE 222

title: Organic Chemistry Laboratory
description: Selected experiments for students taking (or who have taken) CHEM266.
requirementsDescription: Prereq: CHEM 123L or 125L. Coreq: CHEM 266

title: Research Project 1
description: This course is only for exchange students wishing to carry out a research project.

title: Research Project 2
description: This course is only for exchange students wishing to carry out a research project.
requirementsDescription: Prereq: CHEM 392A

title: Research Project
description: Laboratory work on a senior-year research project. Enrolment into this course requires permission of the CHEM494 co-ordinator. See the CHEM494 co-ordinator for course details. CHEM494A/B may not be taken concurrently without prior permission of the CHEM494 co-ordinator.
requirementsDescription: Prereq: Level at least 4A Honours Biochemistry, Chemistry, Chemical Physics, or Materials & Nanosciences, or Medicinal Chemistry students only

title: Research Project
description: A continuation of CHEM494A. CHEM494A/B may not be taken concurrently without prior permission of the CHEM494 co-ordinator.
requirementsDescription: Prereq: CHEM 494A

title: Advanced Research Project
description: This course is only for exchange students wishing to carry out a research project during the spring term.
requirementsDescription: Prereq: Exchange students only

title: Introduction to Scientific Calculations
description: The application of numeric computing software to perform basic calculations, data analysis, regression analysis, plotting of scientific graphs, data manipulation, and equation solving will be covered in this course, with an emphasis placed upon chemical and biochemical concepts and applications.
requirementsDescription: Prereq: CHEM 120 or 121; Not open to Mathematics students

title: Fundamentals of Biochemistry Laboratory
description: Selected experiments for students taking CHEM233.
requirementsDescription: Prereq: CHEM 123L or CHEM 125L; Honours Chemistry or Honours Biochemistry. Coreq: CHEM 233. Antireq: CHEM 237L
